{
  "stem": "6900.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And he wrote and said that he was thankful that-- where I was, and would I [SOBBING] write and tell him what happened.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Because I'd written I was by myself, and what happened to the children and my late husband.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So I went back and told him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "So he got in touch with the Red Cross, and the Red Cross got in touch with Belsen, and they told him that my children, my daughter-- God rest her soul-- and my son were alive in Belsen.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he made arrangements for the children to go to England, but-- and wrote to me to tell me that the children were alive.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Right?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So of course, I was thankful.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So my brother in England sent me some money.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So the first thing I did when I was better, later-- much later-- got something for him to wear, something for my daughter-- God rest-- to wear.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But anyway, that was later.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So he wrote and told me that he was getting the children over.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had a letter from my uncle to tell my dad's youngest brother to-- to say that they were thankful I was alive, but hopes that I'll be strong enough to bear what I still might have to bear.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I didn't understand that for one minute, knowing my children were all right.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I thought my husband was OK.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[SIGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So then, I got a letter when I was on the road to recovery-- that's why I was in the hospital for three months-- to say that my Helen, God rest her soul, had died.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So that put me back in hospital another couple of weeks, you can imagine.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Did they tell you how?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, never told me how.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
